
[1]relaxation

   RELAXA'TION, n. [L. relaxatio.]

   1. The act of slackening or remitting tension; as a relaxation of the
   muscles, fibers or nerves; a relaxation of the whole system.

   2. Cessation of restraint.

   3. Remission or abatement of rigor; as a relaxation of the law.

   4. Remission of attention or application; as a relaxation of mind,
   study or business.

   5. An opening or loosening.
